cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.DC, cs.DL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper proposes novel Rank/Select dictionaries and discusses their performance in terms of query time and size. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper mentions the zero-th order empirical entropy of the set S and uses it as a benchmark for the size of the proposed data structures. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the time complexity of the proposed data structures and compares them to existing implementations. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DL (Digital Libraries) are less likely but still possible categories as the paper discusses the use of Rank/Select dictionaries in various types of data structures such as strings, trees, and graphs.
